					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Don't resize to 292x240, enlarge it to something much bigger, but when you pick a new size for the image, keep it at the same ratio as 294x240.  So you resize from 256x240 to something bigger, and make the image slightly wider at the same time.<br /><br />So if you enlarge it to 1920x1080 for example, you get a size of 1317x1080.<br /><br />If you will be keeping the image small, it's best not to correct the aspect ratio.  But it works well for enlargements.<br /><br />Also, when you resize, you want a resizing algorithm that interpolates the image.</div>
<br />
<br />mmm.. i googled for "image interpolation" and is a big topic. I found a PDF that threat that topic, but is out of my scope, in the sense i can't understand it. It's full of math examples and all things like that.
<br />I also searched for a library or code to do interpolation but there is no one!!. Maybe i should try with a game dev book, something simpler.</div>

					
