				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Also, don't forget that scaling is different on <span class="posthilit">DDraw</span> than D3D (regardless of OS).  There are those of us who do not like the blurry filter crap output when using an emulator, even when using an even number (e.g. display size of 512x448).  I prefer my graphics to look pixellated rather than blurry as shit, but that's also why I use an even multiple (*2) for my display resolution.  Oh, and full screen vs. windowed seems to matter too.  You can look all the many emulators out there which all let you toggle this kind of feature (GPU scaling vs. software); each calls it something different, which amuses me.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

