						<div class="postbody">(Let the record state that that book is <em>Introduction to 3D Game Programming with DirectX 10</em> by Frank D. Luna.)
<br />
<br />The biggest problem that I can see with DirectX 10 is that it's new in Windows Vista, which means 45 percent of people still can't run it according to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Microsoft_Windows#Usage_share" class="postlink">this table</a>:
<br /><div class="quotetitle">Net Market Share wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Windows XP: 44.85%</div>
<br />I already don't have any XP boxes in my home anymore since I replaced the last one with a new PC running Windows 7 nearly a year ago, but my aunt and her kids still have four. It'll take a couple more years (April 2014) for Windows XP to leave extended support.</div>

