						<div class="postbody">The author also wrote DirectX 9 versions of the book: <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Introduction-Game-Programming-Direct-9-0c/dp/1598220160/ref=la_B001JPC4KO_1_1" class="postlink">with shaders</a> and <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Introduction-Programming-DirectX-Wordware-Graphics/dp/1556229135/ref=la_B001JPC4KO_1_3" class="postlink">without</a>.
<br />
<br />IMO, if you're starting now, go for DX10/11, or at the very least, take the shader approach.  Or, if you're really worried about broad platform compatibility, look at OpenGL instead.</div>

